headline: Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings (NCLH) Valuation Check After Latest Annual Revenue And Profit Results
summary: Why Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Stock Is Back on Investors’ Radar Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings (NCLH) has drawn fresh attention after recently posting annual revenue of US$9.69b and net income of US$663.53m. This has prompted investors to reassess how its current share price reflects those results. See our latest analysis for Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings. Despite the fresh earnings spotlight, Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings’ share price has been choppy, with a 4.92% 7 day share price...
